.TH CBSHELL 1 "June 2026" "ConceptBase.cc" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
cbshell \- ConceptBase command-line client shell
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cbshell
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fISCRIPT\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B cbshell
provides a scriptable command-line interface to a running ConceptBase server.
Commands include \fBconnect\fR, \fBtell\fR, \fBask\fR, \fBstartServer\fR, and
\fBexit\fR. Scripts may be piped or passed with \fB-f\fR.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-f " " \fIFILE\fR
Read commands from \fIFILE\fR.
.TP
.BR \-l
Write \fBerror.log\fR and \fBstat.log\fR while running a script.
.TP
.BR \-t
Trace mode (prompt after each command).
.TP
.BR \-i
Start the server in interactive (SWI) mode.
.TP
.BR \-p
Suppress command prompts.
.TP
.BR \-v
Verbose: show server answers.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B CB_HOME
Root directory; must contain \fBcbserver\fR for \fBstartServer\fR.
.TP
.B CB_PORTNR
Default server port (4001).
.SH EXAMPLES
.RS
connect 127.0.0.1 4001
.br
tell "Class A end a in A end"
.br
ask get_object[A/objname]
.br
exit
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR cbserver (1),
.BR cbiva (1)
